<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900413-0010</DOCNO><DOCID>900413-0010.</DOCID><HL>   Lone Star Unit Is Sued   By a Creditor Group</HL><DATE>04/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LSST</CO><IN>BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)</IN><LP>   DALLAS -- Lone Star Technologies Inc. said the unsecuredcreditors committee of its Lone Star Steel Co. unit isseeking to recover $109.3 million from the parent on behalfof the subsidiary.   Lone Star said the committee filed an amended complaint infederal court in Dallas seeking to recover expenditures madeby the unit at the parent's direction and to recover amountsalleged to have been improperly transferred to the parent.</LP><TEXT>   Previously, the committee sought to recover anintercompany receivable valued at a minimum of $23 million onbehalf of the unit, which is operating under protection fromcreditors under Chapter 11 of the federal Bankruptcy Code.   In the lawsuit, the creditors group alleges that theparent orchestrated a series of transactions allowing it touse the steel company's funds for its own benefit. The groupalso seeks to recover assets it said were diverted from thesteel company to Conroe Pipe Co. and to recover the $11.5million that the parent received from the sale of Conroefacilities in December.   Lone Star Technologies said it will defend itself againstthe claims.</TEXT></DOC>